				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\text{t}} \, = \, \left[ {\text{HH}}{_{\text{pix}} \times \, {\text{Dy}}_{\text{hh}} \times \, \eta \, } \right] \, / \, {\text{V}}$$\end{document} where η is the conversion efficiency; V the transported volume (using 0.286l per kWh and 300 l, respectively. Both parameters are derived from4).
